headline: Oil Prices Near Four-Year Lows. Goldman Sachs Sees Opportunity.
summary: Oil prices fell Tuesday and analysts project prices to keep coming down in the coming years. Refining stocks are holding up.

headline: Coinbase downgraded on high valuation as earnings outpace peers
summary: Investing.com -- Argus cut its rating on Coinbase to Hold from Buy, saying the crypto exchange’s valuation has moved too far ahead of traditional exchange operators even as earnings continue to improve.

headline: Gold prices climb on rising Fed interest rate cut bets
summary: Gold prices advanced on Tuesday, buoyed by rising investor expectations that the US Federal Reserve would cut interest rates in December

headline: Asian shares advance after Wall Street gets a lift from hopes for a Fed rate cut
summary: Asian shares mostly gained on Tuesday after U.S. stocks rallied on hopes the Federal Reserve will cut interest rates soon. U.S. futures edged lower and oil prices also declined. Tokyo's Nikkei 225 was nearly unchanged at 48,628.85, after reopening from a holiday.
